        "content": "I’ve completed the requested process for tour J09B:\n\n1. Created `J09B_temp` from `decision_table` with all rows where `TOUR` starts with `J09B` and added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n2. Classified each house (`HAUS`) based on its distinct equipment count:\n   - `< 3` EQUNR → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'KSA'`\n   - `>= 3` EQUNR → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`\n3. Enriched the data:\n   - Joined via `EQUNR` to `eabl`, and from there via `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.` to `eablg` to bring in the meter-reading document number.\n   - Joined to `net_master` and `sales_master` via `EQUNR`.\n   - For each record, preferred `sales_master` customer data when it exists; otherwise used `net_master` data. (Per your instructions, this results in one set of contact fields: when sales data exists, those are used; when only net exists, those are used.)\n4. Exported the final dataset as `J09B.csv` with the specified columns:\n\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n\n5. Sent the CSV to the EVU team at `meter.readings@evu.com` with a short cover note.\n6. Dropped the temporary table `J09B_temp` from the database.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also output the exact SQL used for documentation or reuse.",
